==English==

===Etymology===
Origin unknown; possibly from [[Luger]], [[Lou]], [[Lue]], or [[Louie]]; possibly from the name of the [[baseball]] player [[w:Lou Gehrig|Lou Gehrig]] (from the habit of baseball players of spitting); possible [[variant]] of [[booger]].

====Pronunciation====
*{{AHD|lōōg'i}}, {{IPA|/ˈluːgi/}}, {{SAMPA|/'lu:gi/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{slang}} A thick quantity of [[sputum]], usually containing [[phlegm]].
# {{slang}} Any thick, [[disgusting]] [[liquid]].

[[ru:loogie]]